result.name: workforce-management-information-land-registry
result.notes:
Monthly management information on staff numbers and paybill costs in Civil Service departments, their agencies and their executive NDPBs.
For workforce numbers, both payroll and non-payroll (contingent labour, including consultants) information is provided, split between full-time equivalents (FTE) and headcount, with payroll staff numbers mapped to standard Civil Service grades.
For costs, payroll paybill information is broken down into its component parts i.e. salaries, allowances, employers pensions contributions etc. For non-payroll costs, these are split between costs for consultancy and those of other non-payroll workers.
Staffing numbers are as at the last day of the month for the reference month. Cost information is that for the reference month. For baseline 2014/15 returns, staffing numbers are as at 31 March 2015, and paybill costs are for the financial year 2014/15.

organization.name: land-registry
organization.title: HM Land Registry
organization.description:
HM Land Registry (HMLR) registers the ownership of land and property in England and Wales. It keeps and maintains the Land Register, where more than 29 million titles (the evidence of ownership) are documented.

HM Land Registry is an executive agency of the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy.

https://www.gov.uk/land-registry
